        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 1:59PM EDT by NWS Columbia SC</headline>
        <description>At 159 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Edgefield, or 17 miles north of Belvedere, moving south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Aiken, North Augusta, Belvedere, Edgefield, Johnston, Ridge Spring,
USC Aiken, Edgefield County Airport, Aiken Municipal Airport,
Graniteville, Trenton, Ward, Strom Thurmond High School, Poverty
Hill, Savannah Bluffs Heritage Preserve, Colliers, Vaucluse,
Edgefield Federal Correction Institution, Lick Fork Campground, and
Stevens Creek Public Park.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 20 in South Carolina between mile markers 0 and 26.
Interstate 520 in South Carolina between mile markers 21 and 23.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
